Package: ICtoolkit
Type: Package
Title: Information Criteria for Penalized and Stepwise Model Selection
Version: 0.1.1
Date: 2026-05-22
Authors@R: person("Ryan A", "Peterson", , "ryan-peterson@uiowa.edu", 
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4650-5798")
    )
Description: Provides a unified interface for computing information criteria —
    AIC, AICc, BIC, EBIC, and RBIC — for models of class 'lm', 'glm',
    'glmnet', and 'ncvreg'. For 'glmnet' and 'ncvreg' objects, criteria are
    computed across the full regularization path, returning a vector of values
    (one per lambda). EBIC (Extended BIC) applies a group-size penalty
    controlled by a tuning parameter gamma. RBIC (Regularized BIC) generalizes
    EBIC to structured variable groups, making it suitable for multimodal or
    hierarchically-organized predictors. A stepwise model selection function
    'ic_step()' extends the approach of 'MASS::stepAIC' to support all five
    criteria for 'lm' and 'glm' objects.
